Package nn.models

Class SequentialModel

java.lang.Object
nn.models.Model
nn.models.SequentialModel
public class SequentialModel extends Model
Represents a neural network model structured as a sequence of layers. Each layer's output is fed sequentially as input to the next layer. This is one of the most common architectures for neural networks.

  • Constructor Details

    • SequentialModel

      public SequentialModel(ArrayList<Layer> layers, ModelSettings.executionMode mode)
      Constructs a sequential neural network model with the specified layers and execution mode.
      Parameters:
      layers - A list of Layer objects that make up the model. The layers are processed in the order they appear in the list.
      mode - The execution mode, either SERIAL or PARALLEL, that specifies how the model should be executed.
      Throws:
      RuntimeException - If the provided list of layers is empty or null.
